-- Zimbabwe Platinum Workers Strike Over Power Bills, Mail Reports
-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 2012-01-22T07:15:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-22/zimbabwe-platinum-workers-strike-over-power-bills-mail-reports.html
Workers at Zimbabwe Platinum Ltd.’s
Ngezi mine went on strike demanding the company pay their
household electricity bills, state-controlled  Sunday Mail 
reported, citing Busi Chindove, the company’s head of corporate
affairs.  Calls to the company known as  Zimplats (ZIM)  in Harare weren’t
answered today. Zimbabwe has the world’s second-largest platinum
deposits after neighboring South Africa. Zimplats is 87 percent
owned by Johannesburg-based  Impala Platinum Ltd. (IMP)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
